    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>The Search for Gore's Gore</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>William Dornburgh letter on Richard L Berke's July 9 article suggests Al Gore choose Hillary Rodham Clinton as running mate</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>If Al Gore really wants a vice-presidential candidate who has national recognition and a strong following and who is a Democrat in the Clinton-Gore tradition, the logical choice would be Hillary Rodham Clinton.</p>
        <p>William Dornburgh  Cooperstown, N.Y.</p>
      </block>
